# Solidity Development Rules for Cursor

## Tooling

- Use Foundry Forge - eg. `forge build`

## Code Style

- Use explicit function visibility modifiers (public, private, internal, external)
- Follow Solidity naming conventions: camelCase for variables, PascalCase for contracts
- Use NatSpec comments for all public and external functions
- Implement proper error handling with custom errors instead of revert strings
- Use OpenZeppelin contracts and libraries when appropriate

## Security Best Practices

- Always check for reentrancy vulnerabilities
- Use SafeERC20 for token transfers
- Implement proper access control
- Avoid low-level calls when possible
- Use pull over push payment patterns
- Implement circuit breakers for critical functions

## Gas Optimization

- Use immutable variables for values set at construction
- Pack structs efficiently
- Use assembly sparingly and only when necessary
- Optimize storage layout
- Use libraries for complex operations

## Testing

- Write comprehensive unit tests
- Use property-based testing for edge cases
- Test all error conditions
- Mock external dependencies

## Documentation

- Document complex business logic
- Explain why, not just what
- Keep documentation up to date with code changes 
